results.name: Largest proper divisor of the Fibonacci numbers > 1.
comment: See the list of divisors of positive Fibonacci numbers in the triangle A133021.
See the largest proper divisor of n in A032742.
Fibonacci(1)=Fibonacci(2)=1 do not have proper divisors. - _Emeric Deutsch_, May 18 2008
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 3..1000
example: a(9) = 17 because the 9th Fibonacci number is 34 and the divisors of 34 are 1, 2, 17, 34, then the largest proper divisor of 34 is 17.
maple: with(combinat): with(numtheory): a:=proc(n) options operator, arrow: op(tau(fibonacci(n))-1, divisors(fibonacci(n))) end proc: seq(a(n),n=3..40); # _Emeric Deutsch_, May 18 2008
